        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Freeport, or near Hastings, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ionia...               Hastings...            Lake Odessa...
Saranac...             Freeport...            Woodland...
Clarksville...         Woodbury...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
